  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000100', 'B+', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'The most popular and forgiving cubensis strain worldwide. Origin: Developed by Mr. G in Florida, possibly P. cubensis x P. azurescens hybrid (unconfirmed). APPEARANCE: Large caramel to golden-brown caps (5-15cm), thick white stems bruising blue, dark purple-brown spore print. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.9% psilocybin). YIELDS: Excellent, 3-4 flushes typical, individual fruits can exceed 100g fresh. CHARACTERISTICS: Extremely contamination resistant, tolerates temperature fluctuations (18-28°C fruiting), adapts to suboptimal conditions. Colonization is aggressive and rhizomorphic. Fruits are meaty with good shelf life. Perfect first strain for beginners. Works well on all common substrates (BRF, grain, manure, coir).', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000101', 'Golden Teacher', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'One of the most iconic and widely cultivated cubensis strains. Origin: First appeared in late 1980s, exact origin unknown but believed to be from Georgia/Florida region. APPEARANCE: Distinctive golden-yellow to light orange caps with lighter edges, elegant appearance, medium-sized fruits (5-8cm caps typical), stems white to cream with slight blue bruising. Caps flatten with maturity showing slight umbo. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), known for balanced, insightful effects - hence the "Teacher" name. YIELDS: Good to excellent, reliable 3-4 flushes, medium-sized but consistent fruits. CHARACTERISTICS: Very consistent genetics, rarely produces mutations. Colonization is steady and rhizomorphic. More spiritual/introspective reputation than other strains. Slightly slower to fruit than B+ but very reliable. Excellent spore producer. Works on all substrates. Second-most recommended beginner strain after B+.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000102', 'Cambodian', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 7, 12, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'One of the fastest colonizing cubensis strains available. Origin: Collected by John Allen near Angkor Wat, Cambodia. Tropical Asian genetics adapted to warm, humid conditions. APPEARANCE: Smaller, compact fruits (caps 2-5cm) with golden-brown to caramel coloring. Caps are convex, often with slight nipple. Thin but sturdy stems. Prolific cluster formation. Dark purple-brown spores. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.7% psilocybin), effects often described as energetic and visual. YIELDS: Excellent - what it lacks in individual fruit size it makes up for in numbers. Very prolific fruiter, 4-5+ flushes possible. Fast turnaround between flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: Extremely fast colonization (can complete in 5-7 days). Aggressive, contamination-resistant mycelium. Prefers warmer temperatures (26-30°C colonization, 24-28°C fruiting). Perfect for tropical/warm climates. Very forgiving, excellent beginner strain. Works on all substrates but thrives on enriched formulas. Parent to many fast-colonizing hybrids.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000103', 'Ecuador', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A robust highland strain known for large, dense fruits. Origin: Collected at high elevation (1000+ meters) in the Ecuadorian Andes. Adapted to cooler temperatures than typical tropical cubensis. APPEARANCE: Large, meaty fruits with thick stems. Caps 5-10cm, golden-brown with lighter edges. Well-formed, symmetrical mushrooms. Dense flesh. Slight blue bruising. Dark spore print. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), effects described as balanced and clear-headed. YIELDS: Very good - large individual fruits and reliable flushes. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Handles temperature fluctuation well due to highland origin. Good cool-weather strain. Colonization moderate speed, healthy rhizomorphic growth. Resistant to contamination. Works on all substrates. Excellent beginner strain for those in cooler climates. Very consistent genetics.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000104', 'Mazatapec', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 12, 18, 7, 14, 24, 22, 'A strain with deep ceremonial heritage from the Mazatec people of Oaxaca. Origin: Collected from the Mazatec region of Mexico, associated with traditional shamanic use. Named after the indigenous Mazatec people. APPEARANCE: Classic cubensis appearance - golden-brown caps (4-8cm), white stems, good symmetry. Caps often show slight umbo. Moderate blue bruising. Medium to large fruits. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), traditionally considered more "spiritual" in effect profile - introspective and contemplative. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. Slightly slower to fruit than some strains but consistent. CHARACTERISTICS: Slightly slower colonization than fast strains but very reliable. Prefers moderate temperatures. Excellent for beginners interested in traditional ceremonial strains. Works on all substrates. Consistent, stable genetics passed down through mycological community.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000105', 'PES Amazonian', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A legendary strain from the Amazon rainforest known for large, fleshy fruits. Origin: Collected from the Amazon basin in South America, distributed by Pacific Exotic Spora (PES). Exact collection location unknown. APPEARANCE: Very large, impressive fruits - caps often 8-15cm diameter. Cap color golden-brown to caramel with lighter margins. Thick, substantial stems (often 2-3cm diameter), white with blue bruising. Dense, meaty flesh. Symmetrical, well-formed mushrooms. Dark purple-brown spore print. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), similar to Golden Teacher. Effects often described as grounding and introspective. YIELDS: Excellent - produces large canopies of substantial fruits. 3-4 flushes typical. Individual fruits can weigh 50-100g+ fresh. CHARACTERISTICS: Very reliable and forgiving. Colonization is steady and rhizomorphic. Handles temperature variations well. Works excellently on all common substrates. Excellent beginner strain, especially for those wanting impressive-looking harvests. Very stable genetics.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000106', 'Koh Samui', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 7, 12, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'A fast tropical strain from a famous Thai island. Origin: Collected from Koh Samui island in the Gulf of Thailand by John Allen (Mushroom John). Named after the island known for its full moon parties. APPEARANCE: Smaller, compact fruits (caps 2-5cm typical). Caps are golden-brown with slightly paler margins. Stems thin but sturdy, white with blue bruising. Often fruits in dense clusters. Very fast from pin to harvest. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), often described as energetic and euphoric. YIELDS: Very good - what it lacks in individual size it makes up for in quantity. Prolific fruiter with 4-5+ flushes possible. Very fast turnaround between flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: Extremely fast colonization - among the fastest cubensis strains. Loves warmth (26-30°C). Aggressive, contamination-resistant mycelium. Perfect for tropical/warm indoor grows. Works on all substrates but particularly loves enriched formulas. Excellent for beginners in warm climates.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000107', 'Burma', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 7, 12, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'A fast, reliable strain from Myanmar with excellent colonization speed. Origin: Collected in Myanmar (Burma), Southeast Asia. One of the faster colonizing cubensis strains available. APPEARANCE: Medium-sized fruits with brown to golden-brown caps (4-8cm). Caps are typically convex, becoming broadly convex with slight umbo. Stems white, moderately thick, good blue bruising. Well-proportioned, attractive fruits. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), reliable and consistent effects. YIELDS: Very good - consistent producer with 3-4+ flushes. Fruits rapidly once pinning begins. CHARACTERISTICS: Extremely fast colonization - competes with Cambodian for speed. Very aggressive mycelium that outcompetes contaminants. Tolerant of suboptimal conditions. Works on all common substrates. Preferred for warm/tropical indoor grows. One of the most forgiving strains available. Excellent beginner choice.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000108', 'Costa Rican', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A well-balanced strain from Central America with consistent results. Origin: Collected from Costa Rica in Central America. Tropical lowland genetics adapted to warm, humid conditions. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with classic cubensis appearance. Caps golden-brown to caramel (4-8cm), becoming broadly convex. Stems white, sturdy, good blue bruising. Well-formed, symmetrical fruits. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.7% psilocybin), balanced effects. YIELDS: Good to excellent, very consistent producer with 3-4 flushes. Reliable harvests. CHARACTERISTICS: Excellent beginner strain with consistent genetics. Colonization is steady and healthy. Tolerates warm conditions well. Works on all common substrates. Very stable - rarely produces mutations or abnormal fruits. Low maintenance, high reliability.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000109', 'Treasure Coast', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A Florida strain known for producing occasional albino/leucistic fruits. Origin: Collected from the Treasure Coast region (east coast) of Florida. Named after the famous stretch of coastline. APPEARANCE: Typically golden-brown to caramel caps (5-10cm), but frequently produces leucistic (white/cream) fruits in the same flush - a distinctive characteristic of this strain. Stems white, medium thickness. Good blue bruising. Well-formed fruits of medium to large size. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), consistent effects. YIELDS: Very good - reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. Medium to large fruits. CHARACTERISTICS: Famous for spontaneously producing albino/leucistic variants alongside normal fruits. This genetic instability makes it interesting for breeding projects. Colonization is average speed. Very forgiving and beginner-friendly. Works on all substrates. The leucistic variant can be isolated through cloning (Leucistic Treasure Coast).', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000110', 'Z-Strain', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 7, 12, 5, 10, 26, 24, 'One of the most aggressive and productive cubensis strains available. Origin: Developed through selective breeding for fast colonization and heavy yields. Exact origins unclear but has been circulating since the 1990s. APPEARANCE: Classic cubensis look - golden to caramel brown caps (4-8cm), white stems with blue bruising. Caps are typically convex with slight umbo. Fruits are medium to large sized, well-formed. Dark purple-brown spore print. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), similar to Golden Teacher. Reliable and consistent effects. YIELDS: Excellent - one of the heaviest producing strains. Aggressive fruiting with 4-5+ flushes possible. Known for producing large canopies of uniform fruits. CHARACTERISTICS: Extremely fast colonization (can complete in 7-10 days). Very rhizomorphic, aggressive mycelium that outcompetes contamination. Tolerates temperature fluctuation well. Fruits quickly after colonization. Excellent for beginners and commercial growers. Works on all substrates. Low maintenance, high reward. Parent to JMF (Jedi Mind Fuck). Excellent spore producer.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000111', 'Tidal Wave', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A groundbreaking hybrid that bridges beginner-friendly growth with PE potency. Origin: Created by crossing B+ with Penis Envy, combining the best traits of both parents. Developed by Magic Myco. Parent of the famous Enigma mutation. APPEARANCE: Varies between PE-like thick stems and more traditional caps. Often shows wavy cap edges. Coloring ranges from pale tan to golden brown. Stems thicker than typical cubensis. Good blue bruising. Can show PE characteristics (thick stems, slow-opening caps) or B+ traits (normal caps, easier growth). POTENCY: Above average to high (0.8-1.2% psilocybin), significantly stronger than B+ parent, approaching PE levels. YIELDS: Good - better than PE, nearly as good as B+. Reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: More forgiving than PE while retaining higher potency. Colonization speed moderate. Benefits from casing layer but not required. Can produce unusual mutations including the famous Enigma blob form. Works well on standard substrates. Good spore producer. Excellent intermediate strain for growers ready to move beyond basics.', NULL),

  -- Penis Envy Variants
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000120', 'Penis Envy', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'The legendary high-potency cubensis strain that changed cultivation. Origin: Developed by Steven Pollock in the 1970s from a unique mutation reportedly from Terence McKenna''s Amazon collection. Named for its distinctive phallic shape. APPEARANCE: Thick, dense stems with bulbous, underdeveloped caps that often remain closed or barely open. Pale to light tan coloring, sometimes with bluish tones. Stems are significantly thicker than standard cubensis (2-4cm diameter). Fruits are shorter but extremely dense and heavy. Strong blue bruising. POTENCY: Very high (1.0-1.5%+ psilocybin), consistently 1.5-2x stronger than typical cubensis. One of the most potent cubensis strains available. YIELDS: Lower than standard strains due to slower growth and aborts, but fruits are very dense. 2-3 flushes typical. Quality over quantity. CHARACTERISTICS: Slow colonization, prone to overlay and contamination - requires excellent sterile technique. Prefers slightly lower humidity than most strains. Benefits from casing layer. Poor spore producer (caps rarely open fully) - often propagated by clone. Substrate preference: enriched coir/verm or manure-based. Not recommended for beginners. Parent strain to many popular hybrids (APE, PE6, Melmac, etc.).', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000121', 'Penis Envy Uncut', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'A unique Penis Envy variant where the cap never separates from the stem. Origin: Selected from PE genetics for the "uncut" phenotype where the cap remains attached to the stem throughout development. APPEARANCE: Distinctive appearance where cap edges remain attached to stem, creating a closed or bulbous shape throughout the fruiting cycle. Dense, phallic shape. Pale tan to light brown. Very heavy blue bruising. Often smaller than regular PE but extremely dense. POTENCY: Very high (1.0-1.5%+ psilocybin estimated), on par with or exceeding standard PE. The closed cap may concentrate alkaloids. YIELDS: Low - produces fewer fruits than standard PE. Very dense, heavy mushrooms. 2-3 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Expert cultivation required. Even slower than PE due to unusual morphology. Benefits from casing layer. Rarely produces spores due to cap morphology - clone only. Works on enriched CVG or manure substrates. For collectors and experienced growers seeking maximum potency.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000122', 'Albino Penis Envy', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 16, 24, 12, 21, 26, 24, 'One of the most potent and sought-after cubensis strains. Origin: Leucistic mutation of Penis Envy, developed through selective breeding. Exact origins debated but emerged in the 2000s. APPEARANCE: Ghostly white to pale cream coloration throughout - stems and caps both leucistic (lacking pigmentation). Maintains the classic PE shape with thick, dense stems and small, often unopened caps. Caps may show slight blue/gray tones. Intense blue bruising when handled. Smaller fruits than regular PE but extremely dense. POTENCY: Extremely high (1.2-1.8%+ psilocybin estimated), among the strongest cubensis strains known. Significantly stronger than regular PE. Reports of intense visual and introspective experiences. YIELDS: Low - slower growing with more aborts than regular PE. Fruits are small but very potent (quality over quantity). 1-3 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Very demanding cultivation - requires expert-level sterile technique, precise environmental control. Extremely slow colonization (can take 3-4 weeks). High abort rate. Benefits from casing layer and careful humidity management (too high causes overlay, too low causes aborts). Virtually no spore production - must be cloned for propagation. Not for beginners. Substrate: enriched CVG or manure-based preferred. Parent to many hybrids including Jack Frost, Yeti.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000123', 'Penis Envy 6', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'A more forgiving PE hybrid that retains most of the potency with easier cultivation. Origin: Penis Envy crossed with Texas cubensis. The Texas genetics provide contamination resistance and faster growth while PE contributes potency. APPEARANCE: Thick stems similar to PE but often more developed caps that open more readily. Coloring ranges from pale tan to golden-brown. Stems thick and sturdy. Good blue bruising. More normal cap development than classic PE. POTENCY: High (0.9-1.3% psilocybin estimated), retains most of PE potency while being more accessible. YIELDS: Better than classic PE. 2-3 good flushes typical. Fruits are dense. CHARACTERISTICS: More forgiving than PE - faster colonization, better contamination resistance from Texas parent. Still benefits from casing layer. Produces viable spores unlike some PE variants. Works on standard enriched substrates. Good stepping stone from intermediate to advanced cultivation. Excellent choice for those wanting PE-like potency without expert-level difficulty.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000124', 'Trans Envy', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'A unique hybrid combining PE potency with African Transkei genetics. Origin: Penis Envy crossed with South African Transkei. Combines the potency of PE with the unique visual effects and easier growth of Transkei. APPEARANCE: Thick, PE-influenced stems with caps that show Transkei''s orange-brown coloring. More developed caps than standard PE. Moderate to heavy blue bruising. Fruits are dense and substantial. May show coloring from both parents. POTENCY: High (0.8-1.2% psilocybin estimated), combining PE potency with Transkei''s reportedly unique alkaloid profile. Effects may blend characteristics of both parents. YIELDS: Moderate - better than PE due to Transkei influence. 2-3 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: More forgiving than pure PE. Transkei genetics improve colonization speed and contamination resistance. Benefits from casing layer. Works on enriched substrates. Interesting for those wanting to explore hybrid vigor between African and PE genetics.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000125', 'Melmac', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'The original Penis Envy in its homeomorphic form before stabilization. Origin: Named after the planet from the TV show "ALF" - this represents the original PE genetics as they existed before Pollock stabilized the mutation. Some believe this IS the original PE, preserved. APPEARANCE: Distinctive wavy, alien-looking caps that ripple and fold uniquely. Thick, gnarly stems similar to PE but often more contorted. Caps are more developed than standard PE and show characteristic waviness. Pale to tan coloring with blue bruising. Fruits can be quite large and bizarre-looking. POTENCY: Very high (1.0-1.5%+ psilocybin), comparable to or exceeding standard PE. Among the strongest cubensis varieties. YIELDS: Moderate - better than APE but lower than standard strains. Fruits are dense and heavy. 2-3 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Challenging cultivation similar to PE but slightly more forgiving. Slower colonization than standard strains. Benefits from casing layer. The wavy cap phenotype is genetically stable when cloned. Better spore producer than PE but still limited. Preferred by collectors for unique appearance. Substrate: works well on enriched CVG, manure-based substrates.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000126', 'Enigma', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 21, 35, 21, 42, 26, 24, 'A truly unique mutation that produces brain-like blob structures instead of normal mushrooms. Origin: Emerged as a mutation from Tidal Wave (B+ x PE) genetics around 2020. Does not produce caps, gills, or spores - must be propagated exclusively by cloning. Sometimes called "Brainiac" or "The Blob." APPEARANCE: Forms dense, coral-like or brain-like masses of tissue rather than distinct mushrooms. White to cream colored, often with blue bruising throughout. Texture resembles cauliflower or coral. Can grow quite large (several hundred grams per blob). No gills, no spores, no traditional cap/stem structure. POTENCY: Extremely high (1.5-2.0%+ psilocybin estimated), consistently among the most potent cubensis genetics. Won Psilocybin Cup competitions for potency. YIELDS: Moderate to good by weight, but very slow growing. Single "flush" can take 4-6 weeks. Blobs are very dense. CHARACTERISTICS: Expert-level only - requires patience and precise conditions. Extremely slow development. Benefits from longer colonization before fruiting conditions. Must maintain sterility throughout long grow cycle. Cannot produce spores - clone only propagation. Harvest when growth stalls and blue bruising appears. Very unique collector strain. Substrate: enriched CVG works well.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000127', 'Pearly Gates', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'An albino/leucistic PE variant known for ethereal white appearance. Origin: Selected from PE genetics for leucistic traits. Named for its heavenly white appearance. APPEARANCE: Ghostly white to pale cream coloring throughout. Maintains PE-like thick stems with underdeveloped caps. Smaller than regular PE but very dense. Heavy blue bruising when handled. Ethereal, angelic appearance. POTENCY: Very high (1.0-1.5%+ psilocybin estimated), similar to other PE variants. YIELDS: Low - typical of albino PE strains. Dense, heavy fruits. 2-3 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Demanding cultivation similar to APE. Slow colonization. Benefits from casing layer. Requires excellent sterile technique. Clone propagation recommended due to limited spore production. For experienced growers seeking high-potency leucistic varieties.', NULL),

  -- TAT/True Albino Teacher Variants
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000130', 'True Albino Teacher', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 16, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A beautiful leucistic variant of Golden Teacher that maintains good cultivation traits. Origin: Developed through selective breeding to isolate the leucistic (white/albino) phenotype from Golden Teacher genetics. APPEARANCE: Ghostly white to pale cream caps and stems. Caps maintain the classic GT shape - convex becoming broadly convex, 4-7cm diameter. Stems white with occasional blue bruising. Gills may show pale gray coloring. Spore print is lighter/less visible than standard GT. Beautiful, ethereal appearance. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), similar to or slightly higher than standard Golden Teacher. YIELDS: Good - comparable to Golden Teacher parent. Reliable 3-4 flushes. Fruits are well-formed and consistent. CHARACTERISTICS: More forgiving than APE while sharing leucistic traits. Good beginner-friendly albino strain. Colonization slightly slower than standard GT but still reasonable. Works on all substrates. Good spore producer despite leucistic genetics (spores visible on dark paper). Parent to many popular hybrids including Jack Frost. Foundation strain for leucistic/albino breeding projects.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000131', 'TAT Smurfs', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 16, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A striking TAT variant known for intense blue coloration. Origin: Selected from True Albino Teacher for pronounced blue bruising/coloration. APPEARANCE: White to cream base color with extensive blue staining throughout, especially on caps and upper stems. The blue coloration gives a "smurf-like" appearance. Caps may appear heavily bruised even before harvest. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), the heavy blue staining suggests good oxidation/psilocybin content. YIELDS: Good, similar to TAT parent. CHARACTERISTICS: Similar care to TAT. The blue phenotype is stable and visually striking. Popular for its unique appearance.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000132', 'White Rabbit', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 12, 18, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A visually stunning pure white variety with good potency. Origin: Developed from Albino/leucistic Moby Dick genetics. Named for its pure white appearance. APPEARANCE: Pure white to cream colored throughout - caps, stems, and even gills appear white. Clean, elegant appearance. Caps 4-7cm, stems sturdy. May show faint blue bruising on handling. Very photogenic strain. POTENCY: Above average (0.7-1.0% psilocybin), stronger than typical albino strains. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer with 3+ flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: More demanding than standard strains but easier than APE. Benefits from good sterile technique. Slower colonization than pigmented strains. Beautiful for photography and display. Works well on enriched substrates.', NULL),

  -- Albino/Leucistic Varieties
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000140', 'Albino A+', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'One of the original and most popular leucistic cubensis strains. Origin: Leucistic mutation selected from A+ (A-Strain) genetics. One of the earliest albino/leucistic varieties in cultivation. APPEARANCE: Creamy white to pale caps (5-9cm) that may show faint yellowing or bluish tones. Stems white, moderate thickness. Caps convex becoming broadly convex. Subtle blue bruising. Gills may show pale coloring. Beautiful, clean appearance. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), often reported slightly stronger than standard A+ parent. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer similar to parent strain. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Good beginner-friendly albino strain. More forgiving than APE-type albinos. Colonization slightly slower than pigmented strains but still reasonable. Works on all substrates. Produces visible spores despite leucistic genetics. Parent to several hybrids including Moby Dick. Good choice for those wanting an accessible leucistic variety.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000141', 'AA+', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'An improved or alternate selection of Albino A+ genetics. Origin: Either a different isolation of the same A+ leucistic mutation or a further selected strain. Often used interchangeably with Albino A+. APPEARANCE: White to cream coloring throughout. Caps 5-8cm, convex to broadly convex. Stems white, moderate thickness. Clean, attractive appearance. Subtle blue bruising. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), similar to Albino A+. YIELDS: Good - consistent producer. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Very similar cultivation to Albino A+. Beginner-friendly for leucistic strains. Works on all substrates. The distinction between AA+ and Albino A+ is often unclear in the community - may represent the same or very similar genetics.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000142', 'Moby Dick', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 12, 16, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A impressive leucistic hybrid known for large, white fruits. Origin: Cross between Albino A+ and Golden Teacher. Combines the size potential of GT with Albino A+ leucistic genetics. Named after the famous white whale. APPEARANCE: Large, impressive white to cream colored fruits (caps often 8-12cm+). Maintains GT''s elegant shape. Thick, sturdy white stems. May show faint golden tones at cap center. Dense, meaty flesh. Blue bruising present but subtle against white background. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), similar to parent strains. YIELDS: Good to excellent - bred for large fruits. 3-4 flushes typical. Individual fruits can be substantial. CHARACTERISTICS: More forgiving than APE-type albinos while producing large, impressive white fruits. Slightly slower colonization than pigmented strains. Works on all substrates. Good spore producer. Excellent choice for those wanting large leucistic harvests without expert-level difficulty. Popular for its whale-sized white fruits.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000143', 'Jack Frost', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 12, 18, 7, 14, 24, 22, 'A stunning leucistic hybrid that has become extremely popular since 2020. Origin: Created by a cultivator who crossed True Albino Teacher (TAT) with Albino Penis Envy (APE). APPEARANCE: Striking ghostly-white to pale blue coloration, caps often curl upward at edges resembling snowflakes or frost crystals (hence the name). Dense, thick stems. Caps display beautiful waviness and often have a frosted/sparkling appearance. Heavy blue bruising when handled. POTENCY: Above average to high (0.8-1.2% psilocybin estimated), stronger than Golden Teacher but generally less intense than pure APE. YIELDS: Good, fruits are dense and meaty. Multiple flushes possible. Fruits tend to be medium-sized but heavy. CHARACTERISTICS: More forgiving than APE parent while retaining higher potency. Prefers slightly cooler fruiting temps (20-24°C). Benefits from good FAE to develop characteristic curled caps. Colonization is moderate speed, healthy white mycelium. Spore production can be lighter due to leucistic genetics. Overlay can occur if conditions too humid. One of the most visually striking strains available. Clone-friendly for preserving best phenotypes.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000144', 'Yeti', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'A powerful albino hybrid combining TAT beauty with APE potency. Origin: Created by Jik Fibs by crossing True Albino Teacher with Albino Penis Envy. Combines the best traits of both parents. APPEARANCE: Pure white to cream coloration. Thick, stocky stems reminiscent of PE parent. Caps are more developed than APE, often showing wavy edges. Dense, heavy fruits. Strong blue bruising when handled. Impressive, snow-white appearance. POTENCY: Very high (1.0-1.4%+ psilocybin estimated), stronger than TAT, approaching APE levels. YIELDS: Moderate - better yields than APE due to TAT genetics. 2-3 good flushes. Fruits are dense and heavy. CHARACTERISTICS: More forgiving than APE while retaining high potency. Benefits from casing layer. Slower colonization than standard strains. Requires good sterile technique. Clone-friendly. Substrate: enriched CVG or manure-based preferred. Popular choice for growers wanting PE-like potency with easier cultivation.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000145', 'Ghost', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'An ethereal, ghostly white strain with excellent potency. Origin: Developed through leucistic isolation, exact lineage varies by vendor. Often associated with True Albino Teacher crosses. APPEARANCE: Pale, ghostly white coloration - almost translucent looking. Caps and stems both white to very pale cream. Ethereal, delicate appearance. May show faint blue bruising. Medium-sized fruits with elegant form. POTENCY: Above average to high (0.8-1.2% psilocybin), stronger than most standard strains. YIELDS: Moderate to good. CHARACTERISTICS: More demanding than standard strains. Benefits from precise humidity control. Beautiful display strain. Clone recommended for maintaining phenotype.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000146', 'Avery Albino', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A fast-colonizing leucistic strain combining Cambodian speed with albino genetics. Origin: Leucistic mutation selected from Cambodian cubensis genetics. Combines the fast growth of Cambodian with attractive white coloring. APPEARANCE: White to cream colored caps and stems. Smaller, compact fruits typical of Cambodian genetics (caps 3-6cm). Often fruits in dense clusters. Caps convex with slight umbo. Fast maturation. Moderate blue bruising. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), similar to Cambodian parent. YIELDS: Very good - inherits the prolific nature of Cambodian. 4-5+ flushes possible. Fast turnaround. CHARACTERISTICS: Retains Cambodian''s extremely fast colonization - one of the fastest albino strains. Loves warmth (26-30°C). Aggressive, contamination-resistant mycelium. More forgiving than most albino strains. Works on all substrates. Excellent choice for those wanting an accessible, fast-growing leucistic variety.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000147', 'Great White Monster', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A leucistic strain known for producing large, dense white fruits. Origin: Leucistic mutation selected from Puerto Rican cubensis genetics. The name refers to its large, white, monster-sized fruits. APPEARANCE: Large, impressive white to cream colored fruits. Caps can reach 8-12cm or more. Dense, meaty flesh - very heavy for their size. Thick, sturdy white stems. May show slight blue bruising. Monster-sized fruits give this strain its name. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), similar to or slightly higher than parent strain. YIELDS: Good to excellent - known for large individual fruits. 3-4 flushes typical. Individual fruits can be very substantial. CHARACTERISTICS: Produces impressively large white mushrooms. More forgiving than APE-type albinos. Good colonization speed from Puerto Rican genetics. Works on all substrates. Spore production is reasonable for a leucistic strain. Popular choice for those wanting large, photogenic white harvests.', NULL),

  -- Regional/Wild Origin Strains
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000150', 'Hillbilly', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A classic American strain from the Ozark region known for reliability and rustic charm. Origin: Collected from rural Arkansas in the Ozark Mountain region. Named for its backwoods American origins. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with classic brown caps (5-10cm) that develop a distinctive rustic, earthy appearance. Caps are convex becoming broadly convex, often with visible striations near margins when mature. Stems sturdy, white to cream, bruising blue. Overall appearance is "natural" and wild-looking. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), consistent and reliable effects. YIELDS: Very good - consistent producer with 3-4 flushes. Medium to large fruits. CHARACTERISTICS: Extremely reliable and forgiving. Handles temperature fluctuations well - adapted to variable Ozark climate. Good colonization speed. Works on all common substrates. Very stable genetics. Perfect beginner strain with American heritage.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000151', 'Texas', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A robust Southern US strain adapted to warm conditions. Origin: Collected from Texas, adapted to the hot, humid Gulf Coast climate. One of the classic American regional strains. APPEARANCE: Medium-sized fruits with golden-brown caps (4-8cm). Classic cubensis appearance with convex caps becoming broadly convex. Stems white, moderate thickness. Good blue bruising. Well-formed, symmetrical fruits. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.7% psilocybin), reliable effects. YIELDS: Good - consistent producer with 3-4 flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: Tolerates warm conditions exceptionally well (can fruit up to 28°C). Good beginner strain for warm climates. Colonization is steady. Works on all substrates. Parent to Texas Orange Cap variant and contributor to PE6 genetics.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000152', 'Texas Orange Cap', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A visually distinctive Texas variant with vibrant orange coloration. Origin: Selected from Texas genetics for its distinctive bright orange cap coloration. APPEARANCE: Striking bright orange to rusty-orange caps (4-8cm) that stand out from typical golden-brown cubensis. Caps maintain orange color throughout development. Stems white with blue bruising. Very photogenic strain. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), similar to parent Texas strain. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Same easy-going nature as Texas strain with added visual appeal. The orange color is genetically stable. Works on all substrates. Great for those wanting something visually different while maintaining beginner-friendly cultivation.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000153', 'Gulf Coast', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A subtropical strain from the Florida/Gulf region perfectly adapted to humid conditions. Origin: Collected from the Gulf Coast region of Florida. Adapted to hot, humid subtropical climate. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with caramel to golden-brown caps (5-10cm). Caps often show lighter margins. Stems white, sturdy, with good blue bruising. Well-proportioned fruits. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), consistent effects. YIELDS: Very good - thrives in humid conditions producing reliable flushes. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Excellent for humid grow environments - handles high humidity better than most strains. Fast colonization in warm conditions. Very forgiving. Works on all substrates. Great choice for growers in tropical/subtropical climates or those using humidity-controlled fruiting chambers.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000154', 'Colombian', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A South American strain with robust genetics and reliable performance. Origin: Collected from Colombia, South America. Tropical highland genetics adapted to variable conditions. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with classic brown to golden-brown caps (5-9cm). Caps are convex becoming broadly convex with maturity. Stems white, medium thickness, good blue bruising. Well-formed, attractive mushrooms. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), balanced effects often described as warm and social. YIELDS: Good to excellent - reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. Consistent harvests. CHARACTERISTICS: Handles temperature variation well due to highland origin. Good colonization speed. Very stable genetics. Works on all common substrates. Forgiving and beginner-friendly. A solid, dependable strain.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000155', 'Transkei', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'The first widely available cubensis strain from Africa. Origin: Collected in 2002 from the Wild Coast (Transkei region) of South Africa, in dung near the coast. One of the few documented African cubensis strains. Also known as SAT (South African Transkei). APPEARANCE: Medium-sized fruits with distinctive orange-brown to cinnamon colored caps (4-7cm). Caps often show darker center. Stems white to cream, sturdy. Moderate blue bruising. Good symmetry. Spore print dark purple-brown. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), often described as very visual with body sensations. Unique alkaloid profile due to isolated African genetics. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. Medium-sized but consistent fruits. CHARACTERISTICS: Very unique genetics from isolated African population. Adapts well to cultivation. Good colonization speed. Works on all substrates. Very stable genetics. Parent to Trans Envy (Transkei x PE) and other hybrids. Popular with collectors for its unique origin story and genetics. Effects often reported as distinctive compared to typical cubensis strains.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000156', 'Vietnamese', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 7, 12, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'A fast-growing tropical strain from Vietnam with energetic effects. Origin: Collected from Vietnam, Southeast Asia. Tropical lowland genetics similar to other Asian strains. APPEARANCE: Small to medium fruits with golden to light brown caps (3-6cm). Caps convex with slight umbo. Stems thin but sturdy, white with blue bruising. Often fruits in clusters. Fast maturation from pin to harvest. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), effects often described as energetic, euphoric, and social. YIELDS: Very good - prolific producer with 4-5+ flushes possible. Many smaller fruits rather than fewer large ones. CHARACTERISTICS: Very fast colonization - among the fastest cubensis strains. Loves warmth (26-30°C). Aggressive mycelium. Perfect for tropical/warm indoor grows. Works on all substrates. Excellent beginner strain for warm climates.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000157', 'Ban Hua Thai', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 7, 12, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'A fast Thai strain known for prolific fruiting and reliability. Origin: Collected from the Ban Hua region of Thailand. One of several popular Thai regional strains. APPEARANCE: Small to medium fruits with light brown to golden caps (3-6cm). Classic cubensis shape. Stems white, thin to medium thickness. Often produces dense clusters. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.7% psilocybin), described as uplifting and clear-headed. YIELDS: Excellent - very prolific producer. Multiple flushes with fast turnaround. CHARACTERISTICS: Extremely fast colonization. Loves warm, humid conditions. Very forgiving and contamination resistant. Works on all substrates. Great beginner strain for those in warm climates.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000158', 'Thai Pink Buffalo', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 7, 12, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'A unique Thai strain with a legendary origin story. Origin: Reportedly discovered growing in pink water buffalo dung on Koh Samui island, Thailand. The unusual substrate gives this strain its distinctive name. Also called Pink Buffalo. APPEARANCE: Medium-sized fruits with golden-brown caps (4-7cm) that may show pinkish tones in some lighting. Caps convex becoming broadly convex. Stems white, moderate thickness. Good blue bruising. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), often described as euphoric with creative/artistic effects. YIELDS: Very good - reliable producer with 3-4+ flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: Fast colonization typical of Thai strains. Adapted to tropical conditions. Very forgiving. Works on all substrates. Popular for its unique origin story and reported effect profile. Good beginner strain.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000159', 'Nepal Chitwan', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A unique strain from the Himalayan foothills with excellent temperature tolerance. Origin: Collected from the Chitwan district of Nepal, at the base of the Himalayas. Found in elephant and rhino dung in the jungle-covered lowlands near Chitwan National Park. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with brown to golden-brown caps (5-9cm). Caps show classic cubensis shape with slight umbo. Stems white, sturdy, good blue bruising. Well-formed, symmetrical mushrooms. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), effects described as warm, introspective, and grounding. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. Consistent harvests. CHARACTERISTICS: Exceptional temperature tolerance - handles both warm and cool conditions due to variable Himalayan foothill climate. Can fruit at lower temps than most tropical strains (22-26°C). Good colonization speed. Works on all substrates. Very stable genetics. Great choice for growers with variable temperatures.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000160', 'South American', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A reliable Brazilian strain with consistent performance. Origin: Collected from Brazil, South America. Sometimes called "Brazilian" or "Brazil." Tropical lowland genetics. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with classic brown to golden-brown caps (5-9cm). Well-formed, attractive mushrooms. Stems white, moderate to thick. Good blue bruising. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), balanced effects. YIELDS: Good to excellent - very consistent producer with 3-4 flushes. Reliable harvests. CHARACTERISTICS: Very forgiving and beginner-friendly. Good colonization speed. Tolerates warm conditions well. Works on all common substrates. Stable genetics. Excellent choice for first-time growers.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000161', 'Argentina', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 24, 22, 'A cool-tolerant strain from the southern limits of cubensis range. Origin: Collected from Argentina, one of the southernmost natural habitats for P. cubensis. Adapted to cooler subtropical conditions. APPEARANCE: Medium-sized fruits with light to medium brown caps (4-8cm). Caps convex becoming broadly convex. Stems white, medium thickness. Good symmetry. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.7% psilocybin), reliable effects. YIELDS: Good - consistent producer. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Notably cool-tolerant - can fruit at lower temperatures than most cubensis (20-24°C fruiting optimal). Good for growers in cooler climates or those who struggle with temperature control. Colonization steady. Works on all substrates. Forgiving and beginner-friendly.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000162', 'Australian', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A robust Australian wild collection known for large fruits. Origin: Collected from Australia (exact location varies by source). Australian continent has isolated cubensis populations with unique genetics. APPEARANCE: Large fruits with brown to dark brown caps (6-12cm). Caps are substantial and meaty. Stems thick and white with good blue bruising. Dense, heavy mushrooms. Dark spore print. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), consistent effects. YIELDS: Very good - produces large individual fruits. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Adapted to Australian climate (can handle variable conditions). Robust, contamination-resistant mycelium. Works on all substrates. Good beginner strain. Interesting genetics from isolated population.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000163', 'Hawaiian', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 8, 12, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'A tropical Pacific island strain adapted to warm, humid conditions. Origin: Collected from the Hawaiian Islands. Pacific island genetics with warm-weather adaptation. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with golden to caramel brown caps (5-10cm). Classic cubensis appearance. Stems white, moderate to thick. Good blue bruising. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), effects often described as warm and tropical - euphoric and social. YIELDS: Very good - thrives in humid conditions. 3-4+ flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: Loves warmth and humidity. Fast colonization. Very forgiving. Works on all substrates. Great for tropical/subtropical climates or humidity-controlled fruiting chambers. Easy beginner strain for those who can maintain warm conditions.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000164', 'Puerto Rican', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A Caribbean strain known for dense, meaty fruits. Origin: Collected from Puerto Rico in the Caribbean. Tropical island genetics. Parent to Great White Monster (albino variant). APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with dense, meaty flesh. Caps golden-brown to caramel (5-10cm). Stems thick and white, sturdy. Good blue bruising. Heavy, substantial mushrooms. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.5-0.9% psilocybin), consistent effects. YIELDS: Very good - produces substantial, heavy fruits. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Known for producing dense, meaty mushrooms. Good colonization speed. Works on all substrates. Occasionally produces leucistic variants (which led to Great White Monster selection). Forgiving and beginner-friendly.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000165', 'Cuba', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'The original type locality strain - cubensis was first described from specimens collected in Cuba. Origin: Cuba is the type locality for P. cubensis, meaning the species was first scientifically described from Cuban specimens by Franklin Sumner Earle in 1906. This strain represents genetics from the original habitat. APPEARANCE: Classic cubensis appearance with golden-brown caps (5-9cm) becoming broadly convex. Stems white, moderate thickness. Blue bruising present. Well-formed, symmetrical fruits. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.7% psilocybin), baseline cubensis effects. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Historic significance as the original P. cubensis type locality. Represents "pure" cubensis genetics. Good colonization speed. Works on all substrates. Interesting for collectors and those interested in the species'' history.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000166', 'Jamaica', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 28, 26, 'A Caribbean tropical strain from the island known for its mushroom culture. Origin: Collected from Jamaica, where psilocybin mushrooms have cultural significance and are more openly discussed than in many countries. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with golden-brown caps (5-10cm). Classic tropical cubensis appearance. Stems white, moderate thickness. Good blue bruising. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), effects often described as relaxed and euphoric, fitting the island vibe. YIELDS: Very good - thrives in warm, humid conditions. 3-4+ flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: Loves warmth and humidity. Fast colonization. Very forgiving. Works on all substrates. Popular for its association with Jamaican mushroom culture and retreat centers.', NULL),

  -- Specialty/Unique Strains
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000170', 'Blue Magnolia Rust', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A unique Mississippi strain notable for its unusual rusty-colored spores and higher potency. Origin: Discovered growing wild in Mississippi. Named for the Blue Magnolia region and its distinctive rust-colored spore print. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with golden-brown caps (5-9cm). What makes this strain unique is its rust-orange to rusty-brown spore print rather than the typical dark purple-brown. Stems white with blue bruising. Well-formed fruits. POTENCY: Above average (0.7-1.0% psilocybin estimated), consistently reported stronger than typical cubensis strains. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. Medium to large fruits. CHARACTERISTICS: The rusty spore color is genetically stable and distinctive. Colonization is average speed. More demanding than beginner strains - benefits from good sterile technique. Works on all substrates. Popular with collectors for its unique spore color. Good choice for intermediate growers seeking higher potency.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000171', 'Blue Meanie (cubensis)', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'IMPORTANT: This is a P. cubensis strain, NOT the Panaeolus cyanescens species (also called Blue Meanies). Origin: Australian cubensis strain that shares its name with the more potent Panaeolus species. The name causes frequent confusion. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with golden-brown caps (5-10cm). Caps convex becoming broadly convex. Stems white with pronounced blue bruising - possibly the origin of the "Blue" name. Well-formed, attractive fruits. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), stronger than typical cubensis due to Australian genetics, but nowhere near as potent as true Panaeolus cyanescens Blue Meanies. YIELDS: Very good - reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: Forgiving and beginner-friendly. Good colonization speed. Works on all substrates. The naming confusion is important - always verify whether you have cubensis or Panaeolus, as cultivation and potency differ greatly. This strain''s heavy blue bruising makes it visually striking.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000172', 'Rusty Whyte', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A striking leucistic strain with unusual rusty-orange spore coloration. Origin: Developed from crossing leucistic genetics with rust-spored varieties. The combination creates a unique white-bodied mushroom with rusty spores. APPEARANCE: Ghostly white to cream leucistic fruits with the distinctive rusty-orange spore print. Caps white to very pale cream (5-8cm). Stems white. When spores drop on the white caps, they create a beautiful rust-on-white contrast. Medium-sized fruits. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), similar to other leucistic strains. YIELDS: Moderate to good. CHARACTERISTICS: The combination of leucistic body with rust spores is visually unique and genetically stable. More demanding than pigmented strains - requires good sterile technique. Benefits from precise humidity control. Popular with collectors for unique appearance. Clone recommended for best results.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000173', 'Golden Mammoth', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A carefully developed strain bred for large size, consistent genetics, and contamination resistance. Origin: Developed over 10+ years of selective breeding by a Canadian cultivator (SporePod). Bred specifically for reliability and size. APPEARANCE: Large, impressive fruits with golden caps (7-15cm typical, can exceed 20cm). Thick, substantial stems. Well-formed, symmetrical mushrooms. Dense, meaty flesh. Classic golden-brown coloring. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), consistent effects. YIELDS: Excellent - bred for large fruits and consistent flushes. 3-4 substantial flushes. Individual fruits can be very large. CHARACTERISTICS: Very stable genetics - minimal variation between grows. Exceptional contamination resistance due to selective breeding. Fast, aggressive colonization. Works on all substrates. More consistent than wild-collected strains. Good choice for those wanting reliable, large harvests.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000174', 'Hanoi', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 7, 12, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'A fast-growing Vietnamese strain from the capital city region. Origin: Collected from the Hanoi region of Vietnam. Urban/peri-urban collection. Similar to other Vietnamese strains. APPEARANCE: Small to medium fruits with light golden to brown caps (3-6cm). Caps convex with slight umbo. Stems thin but sturdy. Often fruits in dense clusters. Fast maturation. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), energetic effects typical of Vietnamese strains. YIELDS: Very good - prolific producer. 4-5+ flushes possible. Fast turnaround. CHARACTERISTICS: Extremely fast colonization. Loves warmth (26-30°C). Very aggressive mycelium. Perfect for warm indoor grows. Works on all substrates. Excellent beginner strain for those with warm conditions.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000175', 'Huautla', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 12, 18, 7, 14, 24, 22, 'A strain with claims of connection to Maria Sabina and traditional Mazatec ceremonies. Origin: Named after Huautla de Jiménez in Oaxaca, Mexico - the town where María Sabina conducted veladas (mushroom ceremonies) that introduced Western audiences to psilocybin mushrooms. Whether this strain has direct lineage to those ceremonies is debated. APPEARANCE: Medium-sized fruits with golden-brown caps (4-8cm). Classic Mexican cubensis appearance. Caps often show slight umbo. Stems white, moderate thickness. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), traditionally considered to have introspective, spiritual effects. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. Consistent harvests. CHARACTERISTICS: Slower colonization than fast strains but very reliable. Prefers moderate temperatures. The spiritual/ceremonial associations make it popular with those interested in traditional use. Works on all substrates. Stable genetics.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000176', 'Jedi Mind Fuck', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 16, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A popular higher-potency cubensis strain with disputed origins. Origin: Some claim it derives from a Z-Strain mutation, others suggest it came from a wild Georgia collection. The name references Star Wars. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with golden-brown to caramel caps that often develop wavy edges at maturity. Thick, sturdy white stems with pronounced blue bruising. Caps can reach 5-10cm, often with a pronounced nipple/umbo. Dense, meaty fruits. POTENCY: Above average (0.7-1.0% psilocybin estimated), consistently reported as stronger than typical cubensis strains like Golden Teacher. Known for intense visual and introspective experiences. YIELDS: Good to excellent, reliable producer with 3-4+ flushes. Individual fruits can be large. CHARACTERISTICS: Aggressive colonizer like its Z-Strain parent (if lineage is accurate). Contaminant resistant. Handles temperature variation reasonably well (22-26°C fruiting optimal). Consistent genetics with minimal mutations. Works well on grain spawn to coir/verm or manure substrates. Good choice for intermediate growers seeking higher potency without PE difficulty. Spore prints are reliable and dark purple-brown.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000177', 'Lizard King', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A well-rounded Mexican strain discovered during an outdoor trip. Origin: Reportedly discovered in northern Mexico by a cultivator who found it growing on a mix of wood and horse dung during an outdoor excursion. Named after Jim Morrison of The Doors. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with golden-brown caps (5-10cm). Classic cubensis appearance with convex caps. Stems white, moderate thickness. Good blue bruising. Well-proportioned, attractive mushrooms. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), balanced effects. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer with 3-4 flushes. Consistent harvests. CHARACTERISTICS: Very forgiving and beginner-friendly. Good colonization speed. Handles temperature variation well. Works on all substrates. Stable genetics. Good all-around strain for beginners seeking a classic Mexican variety.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000178', 'McKennaii', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 12, 18, 7, 14, 24, 22, 'A higher-potency strain developed in the Netherlands in honor of Terence McKenna. Origin: Created by Dutch cultivators, reportedly selected for potency and philosophical/visual effects. Named after ethnobotanist and psychonaut Terence McKenna. APPEARANCE: Medium-sized fruits with dark brown caps (4-7cm) that often show distinctive nipple/umbo. Caps are darker than typical cubensis - chocolate to dark brown. Stems white with blue bruising. Well-formed, elegant appearance. POTENCY: Above average to high (0.7-1.0% psilocybin), consistently stronger than Golden Teacher. Known for intense visual and philosophical experiences befitting its namesake. YIELDS: Moderate - not the heaviest producer but fruits are dense. 2-3 flushes typical. Quality over quantity approach. CHARACTERISTICS: Slightly more demanding than beginner strains. Benefits from stable conditions and good humidity. Colonization moderate to slow. Dutch/European origin means it handles cooler temperatures well. Popular in European cultivation scene. Works well on enriched substrates.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000179', 'Orissa India', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 28, 26, 'A distinctive Indian strain known for its tall stature and unique origin. Origin: Collected from the Orissa (now Odisha) state of eastern India. Found growing in elephant dung in the region. APPEARANCE: Notably tall fruits with long, elegant stems. Caps golden-brown (4-8cm), often smaller in proportion to stem length. Stems can reach 15-20cm or more. Moderate blue bruising. Slender but well-formed mushrooms. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), effects often described as cerebral and clear. YIELDS: Good - produces many tall fruits. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Very tall growth habit is genetically stable. Loves warmth and humidity. Good colonization speed. Works on all substrates. The elephant dung origin gives it unique genetics adapted to enriched substrates. Good beginner strain for those in warm climates.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000180', 'PES Hawaiian', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 8, 12, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'Pacific Exotic Spora''s Hawaiian variety - a fast, aggressive colonizer. Origin: Distributed by Pacific Exotica Spora (PES), collected from the Hawaiian Islands. One of the more aggressive and fast-colonizing strains. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with golden to caramel caps (5-10cm). Thick, sturdy stems. Dense flesh. Good blue bruising. Well-formed, substantial mushrooms. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), consistent effects. YIELDS: Excellent - very aggressive fruiting with 4-5+ flushes possible. CHARACTERISTICS: Extremely aggressive colonization - one of the fastest. Resistant to contamination due to speed. Loves warmth and humidity. Works on all substrates. Excellent choice for beginners wanting fast, reliable results.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000181', 'Penis Envy x Melmac', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'A potent cross of two legendary PE variants. Origin: Hybrid of classic Penis Envy with Melmac (the original PE homeomorph). Combines traits of both PE lineages. APPEARANCE: Thick, dense stems with wavy, alien-looking caps typical of Melmac parent. May show PE-like bulbous caps or Melmac-style waviness. Pale tan to light brown coloring. Heavy blue bruising. Dense, heavy fruits. POTENCY: Very high (1.0-1.5%+ psilocybin estimated), combining the potency of both parent strains. YIELDS: Moderate - similar to other PE variants. 2-3 flushes typical. Dense fruits compensate for lower counts. CHARACTERISTICS: Challenging cultivation requiring expert technique. Slow colonization. Benefits from casing layer. Must maintain good sterile conditions. Works best on enriched CVG or manure substrates. For experienced growers seeking maximum potency with unique morphology.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000182', 'Stargazer', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 18, 10, 16, 26, 24, 'A high-potency hybrid known for intense blue bruising. Origin: Reportedly developed from crossing potent strains, exact lineage varies by source. Selected for potency and heavy bruising. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with notable blue bruising throughout - caps and stems show intense blue coloration when handled. Caps golden-brown (5-9cm). Dense, well-formed mushrooms. The heavy bruising suggests high psilocybin oxidation. POTENCY: High (0.8-1.2% psilocybin estimated), stronger than typical cubensis. Known for intense, visual experiences. YIELDS: Moderate - quality over quantity. 2-3 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: More demanding than beginner strains. Benefits from stable conditions. The intense bruising makes it visually distinctive. Works on enriched substrates. Good choice for intermediate to advanced growers seeking higher potency.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000183', 'Wollongong', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A reliable Australian strain from the coastal city of the same name. Origin: Collected from Wollongong, a coastal city south of Sydney in New South Wales, Australia. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with brown to dark brown caps (5-10cm). Classic cubensis appearance. Sturdy white stems. Good blue bruising. Dense, well-formed mushrooms. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), reliable effects. YIELDS: Good - consistent producer with 3-4 flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: Robust Australian genetics. Forgiving and beginner-friendly. Good colonization speed. Works on all substrates. Handles variable conditions well. Good all-around beginner strain from the Australian collection.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000184', 'Amazonian PES', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'Pacific Exotica Spora''s Amazon collection - dense, fleshy fruits. Origin: Same as PES Amazonian - collected from the Amazon basin, distributed by Pacific Exotica Spora. This is the same genetics often listed under both names. APPEARANCE: Large, impressive fruits with dense, meaty flesh. Caps golden-brown to caramel (8-15cm possible). Thick, substantial stems. Heavy fruits. Good blue bruising. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.8% psilocybin), reliable effects. YIELDS: Excellent - known for producing large canopies of substantial fruits. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Very forgiving. Good colonization speed. Handles conditions well. Works on all substrates. Excellent choice for those wanting impressive-looking harvests with beginner-friendly cultivation.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000185', 'Shakti', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'An Indian strain with spiritual significance and above-average potency. Origin: Collected from India, named after the Hindu concept of Shakti (divine feminine creative power). APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with golden-brown caps (5-9cm). Well-formed, elegant mushrooms. Stems white with good blue bruising. Dense flesh. POTENCY: Above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), reportedly stronger than typical beginner strains. Effects often described as spiritual and introspective, fitting the name. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Slightly more demanding than beginner strains. Benefits from good humidity. Works on all substrates. Popular with those interested in the spiritual/ceremonial aspects. Named for the Hindu goddess, suggesting traditional significance.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000186', 'Tasmanian', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 24, 22, 'A cool-tolerant Australian strain from the island of Tasmania. Origin: Collected from Tasmania, the island state south of mainland Australia. Adapted to the cooler Tasmanian climate. APPEARANCE: Medium-sized fruits with brown caps (4-8cm). Classic cubensis appearance. Stems white, moderate thickness. Good blue bruising. POTENCY: Moderate (0.5-0.7% psilocybin), consistent effects. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Notably cool-tolerant - adapted to Tasmania''s temperate climate. Can fruit at lower temperatures than most cubensis (20-24°C). Good for growers in cooler climates. Colonization steady. Works on all substrates. Forgiving and beginner-friendly.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000187', 'Trinity', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'A potent three-way hybrid with impressive lineage. Origin: Created by crossing Penis Envy with Aztec God, some sources suggest additional strains involved. The name "Trinity" refers to the three-strain lineage. APPEARANCE: Thick, dense fruits with PE-like characteristics. Caps may be slow to open. Stems thick and white with heavy blue bruising. Dense, heavy mushrooms. Morphology varies but tends toward PE traits. POTENCY: High (0.9-1.3% psilocybin estimated), significantly stronger than typical cubensis due to PE genetics. YIELDS: Moderate - typical of PE-influenced strains. 2-3 flushes. CHARACTERISTICS: Challenging cultivation similar to PE. Slow colonization. Benefits from casing layer. Requires good sterile technique. Works best on enriched substrates. For advanced growers seeking high potency with unique genetics.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000188', 'Aztec God', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A Mexican strain with claims of above-average potency and ceremonial significance. Origin: Named after the Aztec deities, suggesting ceremonial/spiritual use. Collected from Mexico. APPEARANCE: Medium to large fruits with dark brown to chocolate colored caps (5-10cm). Caps often darker than typical cubensis. Stems white, sturdy. Good blue bruising. Well-formed mushrooms with spiritual aesthetic. POTENCY: Above average (0.7-1.0% psilocybin estimated), stronger than typical cubensis strains. YIELDS: Good - reliable producer. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: More demanding than beginner strains. Benefits from stable conditions. Works on all substrates. Parent to Trinity and other hybrids. Popular with those interested in ceremonial use. Darker cap coloration is distinctive and stable.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000189', 'Albino Goldies', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A leucistic variant of Golden Teacher with attractive white coloration. Origin: Selected from Golden Teacher genetics for leucistic (white/cream) phenotype. Also called Leucistic Golden Teacher or LGT. APPEARANCE: Ghostly white to cream colored caps and stems. Maintains GT''s elegant shape. Caps 5-8cm, convex becoming broadly convex. May show faint golden tones at cap center. Subtle blue bruising. Beautiful, ethereal appearance. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin), similar to Golden Teacher parent, possibly slightly higher. YIELDS: Good - similar to GT parent. 3-4 flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: More demanding than standard GT - requires better sterile technique. Benefits from precise humidity control. The leucistic trait is stable. Works on all substrates. Beautiful strain for those wanting GT characteristics with albino aesthetics.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000190', 'Ochraceocentrata', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 16, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'A less common but intriguing cubensis strain. Origin: Named after the rare African species P. ochraceocentrata (Guzmán), but this cultivated strain is P. cubensis - likely collected from Africa or bred to resemble the wild species. The name means "ochraceous (yellow-brown) center". APPEARANCE: Medium-sized fruits with distinctive coloration - caps show golden-brown to ochre coloring, especially prominent at center (hence the name), fading to lighter tan at margins. Caps 4-8cm typical, convex becoming broadly convex with age. Stems white to cream, moderate thickness, bruising blue. POTENCY: Moderate to above average (0.6-0.9% psilocybin estimated). Reports suggest smooth, warm experience. YIELDS: Moderate, not the heaviest producer but consistent. 2-3 good flushes typical. CHARACTERISTICS: Colonization speed is average to slightly slow. Benefits from higher humidity. More sensitive to contamination than beginner strains - clean technique important. Interesting genetics for collectors and those seeking less common varieties. Substrate flexible but does well on manure-based mixes. African genetic heritage makes it unique among commonly cultivated strains.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000191', 'A-Strain', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'Also known as A+. Fast colonizer, consistent producer. Origin unknown but longtime favorite.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000192', 'Alacabenzi', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'Alabama x Mexican hybrid. Large fruits with thick stems. Very forgiving, good for beginners.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000193', 'Malabar', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 28, 26, 'Indian coast origin. Large dense fruits, very meaty. Prolific producer.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000194', 'Malabar Coast', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'beginner', 10, 14, 7, 14, 28, 26, 'Variant of Malabar from Indian coast. Excellent yields.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000195', 'PE7', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'advanced', 14, 21, 10, 18, 26, 24, 'Penis Envy variant. Similar potency to classic PE. Thick stems.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000196', 'Tidal Wave 2', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 16, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'Second generation Tidal Wave. PE x B+ hybrid. Higher potency than original.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000197', 'Leucistic Burma', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 7, 14, 5, 10, 28, 26, 'White/cream Burma variant. Fast colonization, attractive appearance.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000198', 'Leucistic Golden Teacher', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 16, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'Leucistic variant of Golden Teacher. Pale cream caps.', NULL),
  ('00000000-0000-0000-0001-000000000199', 'Leucistic Treasure Coast', 'Psilocybe cubensis', 'intermediate', 10, 16, 7, 14, 26, 24, 'White variant of Treasure Coast. Florida origin.', NULL),

